title.narrative: YOUTH INNOVATION LAB

description.narrative: Youth Innovation Lab functional and able to foster innovative solutions for youth affected by poverty, adversity and exclusion, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Communication And Advocacy, Cross-Sectoral - Human Rights, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas, Economic And Social Policy General, Human Rights Institutions, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Girls and boys, especially those affected by poverty, adversity and exclusion, progressively utilise quality, inclusive and efficient education system reinforced by policies, programmes and services for empowerment and participation, by 2022.

title.narrative: Youth Innovation Lab functional and able to foster innovative solutions for youth affected by poverty, adversity and exclusion

description.narrative: Adolescent girls and boys benefited from mental health and wellbeing programmes developed by the Youth Innovation Lab as a response to the COVID-19 pandemic and skills building programmes such as UPSHIFT and Study Buddy. Adolescents and youth with disabilities were supported through a cooperation with the Association of Youth with Disabilities and the programme with Special Olympics Montenegro. The programme supporting school-to-work transition called “Prilike” (Opportunities) was expanded for adolescents in the final 2 years of high school.;; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2022
